        ". After the court exits, Hamlet despairs of his fathers death and his mothers hasty remarriage. Learning of the ghost from Horatio, Hamlet resolves to see it himself.        As Poloniuss son Laertes prepares to depart for a visit to France, Polonius offers him advice that culminates in the maxim to thine own self be true.  Poloniuss daughter, ": null
