        " by drinking the dregs of Gertrudes poisoned wine, but Hamlet begs him to live on and tell his story. Hamlet dies in Horatios arms, proclaiming the rest is silence . Fortinbras, who was ostensibly marching towards Poland with his army, arrives at the palace, along with an English ambassador bringing news of Rosencrantz and Guildensterns deaths. Horatio promises to recount the full story of what happened, and Fortinbras, seeing the entire Danish royal family dead, takes the crown for himself and orders a military funeral to honour Hamlet.               Hamlet-like legends are so widely found that the core hero-as-fool theme is possibly ": null
